    <!-- INTRO -->
    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
    <p>
      The Sermon Committee works to support the spiritual growth of our congregation
      through coordinated teachings, scriptural clarity, and faithful Orthodox instruction.
      Its purpose is to strengthen the spiritual foundation of the Ethiopian Orthodox
      Tewahedo community in Belgium.
    </p>

    <!-- RESPONSIBILITIES -->
    <h2>Main Responsibilities</h2>

    <div class="service-box">
      <h3>Organizing Weekly & Feast-Day Teachings</h3>
      <p>
        The committee assists clergy in preparing and coordinating sermons that follow the
        liturgical calendar and uphold the sacred teachings of the Church.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="service-box">
      <h3>Faith Education Programs</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Bible study sessions for adults and youth.</li>
        <li>Introductory teachings for new believers.</li>
        <li>Doctrinal studies based on Church Tradition.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="service-box">
      <h3>Educational Materials</h3>
      <p>
        The committee prepares study notes, lesson booklets, and spiritual learning materials
        in Amharic and other local languages to assist the faithful in their spiritual journey.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="service-box">
      <h3>Seasonal & Special Programs</h3>
      <p>
        During fasting seasons and major feast days, the committee helps coordinate
        dedicated spiritual programs, reflections, and group teachings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- CONTACT -->
    <h2>How We Serve You</h2>

    <div class="service-box">
      <h3>Spiritual Questions & Guidance</h3>
      <p>
        Members of the Sermon Committee are available to help direct individuals to
        clergy for deeper spiritual questions, doctrinal explanations,
        or personal guidance.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
